  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Screening and Prevention Activities to Support EVD Preparedness in South Sudan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this IOM project is to contribute towards EVD preparedness efforts in South Sudan through screening and prevention activities at key points of entry to the country (PoE). With this CERF grant, IOM will procure and distribute screening consumables at 18 sites and will improve WASH facilities in three PoE and 3 health facilities. The project will last six months and will benefit 232,572 including 132,566 women and girls.</narrative>
  </description>
